## How this dashboard works

- Every issue here is **self-contained** — files to touch, expected outcome, acceptance criteria, verification command all inline. No need to read other docs to start work.
- Issues are labeled with `layer:*`, `bucket:*`, `criticality:*`, `milestone:m1`–`m5`, plus `ready` or `blocked`.
- `ready` = no unmet dependencies. `blocked` = waiting on predecessor issues.
- When a predecessor closes, run `/test-publish --refresh` to re-evaluate `ready` / `blocked` labels.
- To pick the next workable issue: `gh issue list --search "label:test-readiness label:ready sort:created-asc" --limit 1`.
